body: This issue is lacking enough information for us to be able to fully understand what is happening. Please attach a small, runnable project or post a small, runnable code listing that reproduces what you are seeing so that we can investigate.

@ajcvickers  I've attached a small example weatherforecast api project to reproduce this.

Here are the instructions:
- In `Season.cs` add a new property ie. `public string Random { get; set; }`
- Add new migration with EF Commands
- Rollback the migration with EF Commands

After rollback, `MyContextModelSnapshot.cs` should contain changes with the hashtag described earlier.

[MigrationRepro.zip](https://github.com/dotnet/efcore/files/13635883/MigrationRepro.zip)
Note for triage: still repros on 8.0.

While these changes are not intended, they shouldn't result in any functional difference. I.e. the next migration will be generated normally. So, you can push them as is or you can add a new (empty) migration and just keep the updated model snapshot.
Thanks, I've tested, and adding the next migration works normally.

issue.title: Upgrade the snapshot when rolling back to a migration from a previous version
